The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Nov. 19 (PTI): Nearly 93 million people will live in slums by next year, the number having risen by almost a quarter in the last decade.          
	A committee of experts, formed to assess the figure, has projected the population at 93.06 million in 2011, an increase of 23.7 per cent since 2001, the government said today The body has recommended including cities with populations less than 20,000 in the count.                  
	 Kochi (PTI): A former army officer who was sacked following a court martial order 25 years ago will be paid the full salary and pension due till his retirement. The Armed Forces Tribunal has directed the Centre to clear the arrears within six months.                  
	Bulandshahar (PTI): Poachers have allegedly killed two Gangetic dolphins at an Uttar Pradesh wetland designated as having international significance. Local residents said one body was found in the Ganga and another on the riverbank in Ramsar.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Sheila Dikshit has sought greater focus on moral education in city schools, saying that society needs honest and upright citizens for its progress. Delhis chief minister noted the Centres sincere efforts in the last ten years to improve educational infrastructure.           
	Court arson          
	Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Unidentified people set a court record room on fire at Kairana, Uttar Pradesh, burning 90 files pertaining to criminal cases, police said today. The related hearings have been postponed till copies are reconstructed.                                                                                                                                              
